Package: cytoverse
Title: Easily Install and Load the 'cytoverse'
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    c(person(given = "Mike",
             family = "Jiang",
             role = c("aut", "cre"),
             email = "wjiang2@fredhutch.org"))
Description: The 'cytoverse' is a set of packages that are commonly used for cytometry data analysis. 
            This package is designed to make it easy to install and load
    multiple 'cytoverse' packages in a single step. Learn more about the
    'cytoverse' at <https://cytoverse.org>.
License: GPL-3
URL: http://cytoverse.org,
    https://github.com/RGLab/cytoverse
BugReports: https://github.com/RGLab/cytoverse/issues
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.1)
Imports: 
    flowCore (>= 1.43.10),
    flowWorkspace (>= 3.28.12),
    openCyto (>= 1.11.3),
    ncdfFlow,
    ggcyto (>= 1.9.4),
    CytoML (>= 1.8.1),
    crayon
Suggests: 
    covr,
